>Description:
Hi, I love to use Racket and OSX. and thanks to you guys for this great DrRacket. :-)

When I use DrRacket in MS-Windows, it correctly supports Korean IME.

But when I input some Korean Characters in OSX, it inserts only last character before I press space or other non-Korean char-keys.
>How-To-Repeat:
If I type "gksrmf"("한글") in Korean IM mode, it suppose to be "한글" but, In OSX, no characters appeared in screen.

If I type "gksrmf "("한글 ") in Korean IM mode, it only entered "글 ".
